# Professional copy tone (founder tone law)

Applies to **all** agent writing for The Landscape Archive Foundation (`.org`) and any Archive-adjacent copy touched from this repo: public pages, UI, user-facing-adjacent docs.

Canonical twin also lives in `la-frontend/.cursor/rules/professional-copy-tone.mdc` (keep wording aligned when editing).

## Do

- Professional, calm, straight to the point.
- Status facts are fine: draft, waitlist, not accepting entries, empty / sparse programmes — state them plainly.
- Soft-launch honesty (Archive): emptiness and hold truths without attitude. **Honesty ≠ snide.** See sibling `la-frontend/.cursor/rules/soft-launch-honesty.mdc`.

## Never

| Ban | Meaning |
|-----|---------|
| Dismissive framing | “not as branding wallpaper”, “not a decksheet”, “rather than wallpaper”, “unlike a brochure” |
| Passive-aggressive | Digs at imagined audiences, competitors, or “people who don’t get it” |
| Sarcasm / smart-arse | Winks, eye-rolls, clever put-downs |
| Defensiveness | Disclaimer walls; “we are not X” throat-clearing that dominates the line |

## Anti-examples → preferred

| Avoid | Prefer |
|-------|--------|
| “This is not branding wallpaper.” | “Photography supports the specimen record.” |
| “Not a decksheet — real plant data.” | “Species records with measured traits and sources.” |
| “Unlike a brochure site…” | Lead with what the programme *is*; skip the foil. |
| “We’re not vaporware / not just marketing.” | Ship status: “Draft.” / “Not accepting entries.” / “Waitlist open.” |
| “Empty because others fake it.” | “This section is empty until the next intake.” |

## Checklist before shipping copy

1. Does any sentence exist mainly to reject a lesser category (wallpaper, brochure, deck)? Delete the reject; keep the claim.
2. Would a calm founding member say this out loud to a peer or funder? If not, rewrite.
3. Status / emptiness: fact only — no moral superiority.
